issue.body:
## Subject of the issue

Problem with rwindow.draw();

## Your environment

### Laptop #1

Linux 4.18.0-11-generic x86_64 / Kubuntu 18.10 / Dolphin / AMD ATI Radeon R7 M265/M365X/M465 / Mesa 18.2.2
SFML 2.5.1
gcc 8.2.0
no special flags

### Laptop #2

Linux 4.18.0-11-generic x86_64 / Kubuntu 18.10 / Dolphin / UHD Graphics 630 / Mesa 18.2.2
SFML 2.5.1
gcc 8.2.0
no special flags

### Laptop #3

Linux 4.18.0-11-generic x86_64 / Kubuntu 18.10 / Dolphin / nVidia GTX 950m / nVidia driver v394 (or smth like this)
SFML 2.5.1
gcc 8.2.0
no special flags

## Steps to reproduce

1. create render window
2. load texture
3. create sprite from texture
4. draw sprite with window.draw()

```cpp
#include <SFML/Graphics.hpp>
#include <thread>

sf::RenderWindow * createWindow(const std::string &title, uint width, uint height) {
  auto* window = new sf::RenderWindow();

  sf::VideoMode vm(width, height, 16);

  sf::ContextSettings settings;
  settings.antialiasingLevel = 4;
  settings.majorVersion = 3;
  settings.minorVersion = 3;
  settings.depthBits = 24;
  settings.attributeFlags = sf::ContextSettings::Core;

  window->setVerticalSyncEnabled(true);
  window->create(vm, title, sf::Style::Default, settings);

  return window;
}

int main () {
  auto* window = createWindow("tmp", 800, 600);

  sf::Texture texture;
  texture.loadFromFile("texture.png");

  sf::Sprite sprite;
  sprite.setTexture(texture);

  window->clear(sf::Color::Black)
  window->draw(sprite);
  window->display();

  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1000));

  texture.copyToImage().saveToFile("saved.png");

  return 0;
}
```

## Expected behavior

Expected sprite to be drawn, and the image to be saved.

## Actual behavior

Nothing is drawn except of black screen and no errors are yelled.
Image is saved successfully, so the problem is not in file/image/texture loader.
